    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#robinson1913"/>, pp. 179-180, n. <citedRange>55</citedRange>, fig. 37</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 113, n. <citedRange>93</citedRange>, fig. 49</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.205</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>024900</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, p. <citedRange>204</citedRange> (date of the base)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>138</citedRange> (probable provenance)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.64</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63721"><name nymRef="#Ἐπιτέλης">Ἐπιτέλης</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64906"><name nymRef="#Λῦσις" type="patronymic">Λύσιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2"><lem resp="#oliverioDAI2">Λύσιος</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#robinson1913">Λυσίο<supplied reason="omitted">υ</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Epitelès fils de Lysis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Epiteles son of Lysis.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Epiteles figlio di Lysis.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Robinson had no information about the provenance. This seems to show that the base was found in situ by De Cou in 1911. As the Norton mission does not seem 
                    to have explored other parts of the necropoleis, the Thorns supposed that the provenance is the North Necropolis and it is probably so.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
